## Data from sports-reference.com

dadata <- read_html("https://www.sports-reference.com/cbb/conferences/big-east/2023-stats.html#conference-stats", header = FALSE)

dat <- html_table(dadata, fill = TRUE)

dataa <- data.frame(dat)
write.csv(dataa, file="~/documents/markdownfiles/bigeast.csv")

data <- read.csv(file = "~/documents/markdownfiles/bigeast.csv", skip = 1, header = TRUE, as.is = TRUE)

## cleaning the data

data[data == ''] <- NA
data[data == 'Player'] <- NA

data <- data %>% drop_na(Player)

cols <- colnames(data)
data <- data %>% mutate_at(cols[7:27], as.numeric)

data <- subset(data, MP > 25)

data$Team <- toupper(substr(data$School,1,3))

####

data <- data %>% arrange(PTS)
data$Count = 1:nrow(data)
data$PTSPERC <- ((data$PTS)/(sum(data$PTS)))

data$CUMSUMPTS <- cumsum(data$PTSPERC)

data <- data %>% 
  count(Count) %>% 
  mutate(Cum = cumsum(n)/sum(n)) %>% 
  select(-n) %>% 
  right_join(data) %>%
  select(names(data), everything())
## Joining, by = "Count"
## splits

s <- split(data,data$Team)

teams <- c(sort(unique(data$Team)))

for (i in 1:length(teams)){
  assign(teams[i], s[[i]])
}

teams <- list(BUT, CON, CRE, DEP, GEO, MAR, PRO, SET, ST., VIL, XAV)

schools <- unique(data$Team)


###### Functional Programming ##

## func for bar dist chart

distplot <- function(team){
  namai <- deparse(substitute(team))
  
  print(ggplot(team, mapping = aes(x = reorder(Player, PTS),PTS))+
          geom_bar(stat = "identity", width = .5,fill="royalblue")+
          scale_x_discrete(guide = guide_axis(n.dodge = 3))+
          ylab("Points")+
          xlab("")+
          theme_minimal()+
          labs(title = paste(namai," -  Points Distribution")))
}

## func for Lorenz curve & GINI 

lorenz <- function(team){
  
  namai <- deparse(substitute(team))
  
  print(ggplot(team, aes(x = Cum, y = CUMSUMPTS))+
    geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1)+
    geom_smooth() + 
    ylab("Quartiles of Points")+
    xlab("Quartiles")+
    theme_minimal()+
      labs(title = paste(namai ," -  Lorenz Curve"))+
    annotate("text", x=.25, y=.82, label = paste("GINI coeff",signif(Gini(team$PTS),4))))
  
  Gini(team$PTS)
}

#### school level ANALYSIS

schdata <- data.frame(c(schools))

for (i in 1:length(teams)){
  schdata[i,2] <- sum(teams[[i]][["TOV"]])
  schdata[i,3] <- sum(teams[[i]][["AST"]])
  schdata[i,4] <- sum(teams[[i]][["PTS"]])
  schdata[i,5] <- Gini(teams[[i]][["PTS"]])
    
}


colnames(schdata)[2] = "tov"
colnames(schdata)[3] = "ast"
colnames(schdata)[4] = "pts"
colnames(schdata)[5] = "gini"
